nvidia-graphics-drivers-375 (375.39-0ubuntu1) zesty; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release:
    - Added support for the following GPU(s):
        Quadro GP100
        Quadro P4000
        Quadro P2000
        Quadro P1000
        Quadro P600
        Quadro P400
        Quadro M1200
        Quadro M2200
    - Fixed a bug that caused system hangs when resuming from suspend
      with some GPUs.
    - Fixed a regression that could cause corruption when hot-
      plugging displays.
    - Fixed a regression that prevented systems with multiple
      DisplayPort monitors from resuming correctly from suspend.
  * debian/dkms_nvidia/patches/buildfix_kernel_4.10.patch,
    debian/templates/dkms_nvidia.conf.in:
    - Add support for Linux 4.10.

 -- Alberto Milone <alberto.milone@canonical.com>  Wed, 15 Feb 2017 16:10:22 +0100

